
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Discourse and Institutions
AU  - Phillips, Nelson
AU  - Lawrence, Thomas B.
AU  - Hardy, Cynthia
Y1  - 2004/10/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2004.14497617
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2004.14497617
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 635
EP  - 652
VL  - 29
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We argue that the processes underlying institutionalization have not been investigated adequately and that discourse analysis provides a coherent framework for such investigation. Accordingly, we develop a discursive model of institutionalization that highlights the relationships among texts, discourse, institutions, and action. Based on this discursive model, we propose a set of conditions under which institutionalization processes are most likely to occur, and we conclude the article with an exploration of the model's implications for other areas of research.
AB  - We argue that the processes underlying institutionalization have not been investigated adequately and that discourse analysis provides a coherent framework for such investigation. Accordingly, we develop a discursive model of institutionalization that highlights the relationships among texts, discourse, institutions, and action. Based on this discursive model, we propose a set of conditions under which institutionalization processes are most likely to occur, and we conclude the article with an exploration of the model's implications for other areas of research.
